\begin_layout Definition
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{X}=(\sam Xn)^{T}$
\end_inset

 be a random sample from a population 
\begin_inset Formula $X\sim f(x|\theta)$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\bx=(\sam xn)^{T}$
\end_inset

 be the observed values, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 be an unknown parameter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
Suppose that we can find 
\begin_inset Formula $L(\boldsymbol{X})$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U(\boldsymbol{X})$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P(L(\boldsymbol{X})\le\theta\le U(\boldsymbol{X}))=1−α
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
Then 
\begin_inset Formula $[L(\bx),U(\bx)]$
\end_inset

 is called a 
\series bold
\emph on
confidence interval
\series default
\emph default
 for 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $(1−α)\%$
\end_inset

 is called the
\series bold
 
\emph on
confidence level
\series default
\emph default
.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $α=0.05$
\end_inset

 is a standard 95% confidence interval.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
