This is incorrect, CIs are part of the frequentist paradigm and as such
 the population parameter is fixed but unknown.
 Consequently, the probability any given CI contains the true value must
 be 0 or 1 (it does or does not).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
A narrower confidence interval is always better.
