\begin_layout Frame
To obtain a confidence interval for 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

, note that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Q(\bX,\mu)=\frac{\Xbar-\mu}{{\rm SE}(\Xbar)}\sim N(0,1)
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula ${\rm SE}(\Xbar)=\sigma/\sqrt{n}$
\end_inset

 is the 
\emph on
standard error
\emph default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Xbar$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P\big(-z_{1-\alpha/2}\le Q(\bX,\mu)\le z_{1-\alpha/2}\big)=1-\alpha
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P\big(\Xbar-z_{1-\alpha/2}{\rm SE}(\Xbar)\le\mu\le\Xbar+z_{1-\alpha/2}{\rm SE}(\Xbar)\big)=1-\alpha
\]

\end_inset

Hence, the 
\begin_inset Formula $(1-\alpha)$
\end_inset

 CI for 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
CI_{1-\alpha}(\mu)=\big[\xbar-z_{1-\alpha/2}\frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{n}},\xbar+z_{1-\alpha/2}\frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{n}}\big]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

